==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|ang|hider}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*hidrê}}. Cognate with {{cog|la|citer}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/ˈhɪðə/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/ˈhɪðɚ/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-hither.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|en|ɪðə(r)}}

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# {{lb|en|literary|or|archaic}} To this place, to here.
#: {{ux|en|He went '''hither''' and thither.}}
# [[over]] [[here]]

====Usage notes====
* Compare to the [[pronominal adverb]] "[[hereto]]" which follows the pattern of "preposition + what" or "preposition + which".

